)Attr Default(%+_)
/* % type(text  ) intens(high)              Defaults displayed for */
/* + type(text  ) intens(low )                   information only  */
/* _ type( input) intens(high) caps(on ) just(left )               */
   ¬ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) color(yellow)
   ! type(output) intens(low ) caps(off) just(asis ) color(white)
   ¦ type(text  ) intens(high) color(white)
   ` type(text) intens(low ) caps(off) just(asis ) color(turq)
)Body
+------------------------% TSO/E-Mail Forward Message +-------------------------
%Command ===>_zcmd
%
`
`    This dialog allows you to forward a message to other individual(s)
`    via electronic mail.
`
%    Field       Description
`
¬    Userid     `The userid(s) or nickname(s) of the intended recipients
`                an '*' may be used to forward the message to the original
`                sender (a better technique for answering messages)
`
¬    Nodename   `The node name to be used if a userid is specified
`                (this field may be blank if you are using a nickname)
`
¬    Forwarded  `If this is 'yes' the forwarded text will be shifted right
`                2 columns and the '>' symbol inserted in column 1.  A line
`                of text will also be inserted before and after the text
`                text to indicate the start and end of the forwarded text.
`
)Init
)Proc
)End
